    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNvim supports opening files with `file://` syntax as a feature of netrw:\n\n```bash\nnvim file:///etc/motd # works\nnvim --cmd 'let g:loaded_netrw = 1' file:///etc/motd # doesn't work\n```\n\nThis means that `file://` is not supported if netrw is not used.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`file://` support is built-in.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "As `file://` are just urls this behaviour should be added to `runtime/plugin/net.lua`\n\nEDIT: doesn't support writing yet, but should be easy enough now that https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38837 has landed",
